{
  "stem": "26728.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I had some of the best instructors at Marana, and then at Thunderbird too in-- in Phoenix, Litchfield.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These men taught us combat training.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and we were flying BT-13s and AT-6s and P-47s.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then when we got through with the-- with the-- became-- flight officer is what they called us at the time-- where we weren't an enlisted man or officer.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were flight officers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Kind of like a warrant officer, in between, and with a promise of a commission.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They send some of us to-- some of that graduating class, now, this is-- this is in the Army Air Corps-- to Long Island for advanced training, combat training.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went to Louisiana.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't remember where I was in Louisiana.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was just-- it was-- I didn't-- I hated the idea of going back there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I went to Louisiana to a-- to an Army-- Army air base in Louisiana for tactic, combat tactical training-- and then went to Boston.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Am-- am I-- am I getting too confusing here?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, this is in the-- this is in the fall or late summer of 1944.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We sailed on the Queen Mary and went to-- and I don't know where we landed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It seems like it was Liverpool, England, but I don't really remember.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The journey was-- because of the-- we were not in a convoy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The ship zigzagged.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went clear down-- from Boston down to Florida and went across the ocean like this.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, that was that-- that-- the Queen Mary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I also went-- and now, that's another story.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
